article.description: No. 19 Georgia clamps down on Coppin State 49-29
article.headline: No. 19 Georgia clamps down on Coppin State 49-29
article.linkText: No. 19 Georgia clamps down on Coppin State 49-29
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. --  Freshman Mackenzie Engram came off the bench to score 20 points and No. 19 Georgia shut down Coppin State 49-29 on Tuesday.

Engram made 7 of 13 shots, including both of her 3-pointers and all four free throws. The rest of the team made just 6 of 37 shots (16 percent) and 1 of 10 3-pointers as the Bulldogs (8-0) shot just 26 percent.

Engram had 11 points in the first half, one shy of her previous best, as the Bulldogs opened at 20-14 lead despite shooting 21.4 percent (6-28).  Georgia forced 16 Coppin State turnovers and the Eagles missed their only free throw.

Then the Bulldogs opened the second half with an 11-0 run, highlighted by five Engram points and turned that into a 17-2 surge with another Engram basket.

Coppin State (1-5) ended up at 25.5 percent with 26 turnovers.

Georgia was 20-31 from the foul line, the Eagles 3-6.
